article.headline: Bradley eases past Jacksonville State 72-65
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. -- Tyshon Pickett had 15 points and 10 rebounds Friday night to help Bradley top Jacksonville State 72-65 in their season openers. Omari Grier led Bradley with 17 points. The Braves led by as many as 10 midway through the second half, but when Brian Williams hit a jumper with 7:28 left, Jacksonville State pulled within 52-51. Walt Lemon Jr., answered with a 3-pointer to make it 55-51 and Jacksonville State never got any closer. Lemon finished with 16 points on 6-for-20 shooting. Grant White had 16 points for the Gamecocks, who shot only 3 for 16 from 3-point range.
